<p>In my example, in a BITCOIN system, would the ownership rights in the BITCOINS be asserted against the owner of the pencil (capitalist interpretation) or the owner of the car (socialist interpretation). If they cannot be asserted against either, they have no value. How does the owner of the BITCOINS realise their value?</p>
